raw_body:
This pull request contains several important bug fixes to the codebase:

1) InvalidMessage exception not being thrown when incorrect field tag is being decoded - this resolves issue with failed 'GarbledMessage' acceptance test cases, for example as in pull #91 ;
2) Memory alignment issues in FIX::integer_to_string() method and with shared_array<> class, issue #46 ;
3) Undefined behavior on some compilers during integer deserialization, issue #82 ;
4) Build error on VS2015, issue #81 ;
5) Double precision issues after deserialization, issue #83 ;
6) Error in SocketConnection::processQueue() when socket error is being reported;
7) Error in FieldMap::removeGroup() reported in issue #53 ;
8) Improvement to data field decoding and error reporting, which can now be decoded in the trailer as well as in body and header;
9) Redundant MSXML import is removed on Windows which enables multithreaded project compilation.

Also several performance improvements are included:
1) Improvement for the container type used to store fields in the message;
2) Use of Florian's Loitsch 'double-conversion' library for double de/serialization. It works ~250-300% faster that CRT functions while retaining the same level of precision. https://github.com/google/double-conversion
3) Small message type verification improvement during parsing.

